
Hi all,
Thank you for sending over the contract. Before I proceed, I need to raise a concern regarding the circumstances of my recruitment and how they relate to the compensation package currently being offered.
When I accepted the internship at Cx, I did so based on a clear and explicit assurance from the recruiter that I would be moved into the Analyst 1 role as soon as a position became available. This was not an informal comment, it was a direct representation made during the recruitment process, and I have a video recording confirming this progression path. I relied on that assurance in good faith, and it was a material factor in my decision to join the company.
Since then, several Analyst 1 roles have opened and been filled without my consideration, despite the earlier assurance. I have now been offered the Associate Analyst position with £20,000 in stock, which is not only materially below the compensation associated with the Analyst 1 role that was represented to me, but also less in stock than last year’s graduate intake and other joiners who have less professional experience in cybersecurity than me. Taken together, this places me at a financial and professional disadvantage compared to both the expectations set during recruitment and the compensation offered to peers in similar entry‑level cohorts.
To resolve this constructively and internally, I would like to propose a remedy that focuses on restoring the compensation and progression expectations I reasonably relied upon. While I am not insisting on immediate placement into Analyst 1, I am requesting a compensation adjustment that reflects the quantifiable difference between the represented Analyst 1 package and the Associate package — approximately £40,000 annually when considering salary (£17,500), bonus (£3,500), and stock (£15,000) that would have been gained as an Analyst 1. 
This adjustment could take the form of a lump‑sum payment, a salary uplift, additional RSUs to align with the originally represented package, or a combination of these.
I would also appreciate a clearly defined and accelerated promotion plan with transparent criteria, so that my progression aligns with the expectations set during recruitment and avoids further disadvantage.
I want to emphasise that I am raising this concern in good faith and with the intention of resolving it professionally and internally. I also understand that employees are protected from detriment or disadvantage for raising concerns relating to recruitment representations, compensation fairness, or progression pathways. My goal here is simply to ensure that the commitments made during recruitment are reflected in a fair and proportionate outcome.
I appreciate that misunderstandings can occur, and I am not making any assumptions about intent. My focus is on aligning expectations and ensuring that the situation is handled transparently and fairly. I am confident that we can reach a constructive resolution that supports my continued growth within Cx.
Please let me know when we can discuss next steps.
Thank you,
Said Juma

