Meeting script:
Opening
“Thanks for meeting with me. I want to resolve this constructively and internally. I’m raising this because the compensation and progression pathway in the contract doesn’t align with what was represented to me during recruitment.”
State the Core Facts
- “I was given a clear and explicit assurance that I would be moved into the Analyst 1 role as soon as a position became available.”
- “This wasn’t a casual comment — it was a direct representation, and I have a recording of that assurance.”
- “I relied on that representation in good faith when deciding to join Cx.”
State the Impact
- “Several Analyst 1 roles opened and were filled without my consideration.”
- “The Associate offer includes £20,000 in stock, which is less than last year’s graduate intake.”
- “This creates a measurable financial and professional disadvantage.”
Neutralise Their Likely Pushbacks
If they say: “There was no guarantee”
→ “I understand that, but the representation was explicit, and I relied on it when making my decision.”
If they say: “We can’t discuss other employees’ compensation”
→ “I’m not asking for details — I’m highlighting a discrepancy that directly affects fairness and consistency.”
If they say: “This is standard for this cohort”
→ “That may be the case, but my situation is not standard because of the explicit assurance made during recruitment.”
If they say: “We can’t adjust compensation”
→ “I’m open to different forms of adjustment — salary, RSUs, or a one‑off payment. The principle is restoring what I reasonably relied upon.”
Present Your Ask
“I’m not insisting on Analyst 1. My preference is a compensation adjustment that reflects the difference between the represented Analyst 1 package and the Associate package, and a clearly defined accelerated promotion plan.”
Assert Your Protection (Subtly)
“I want to emphasise that I’m raising this in good faith. I understand employees are protected from detriment for raising concerns about recruitment representations or compensation fairness.”
Close
“I’m confident we can reach a fair and reasonable outcome. What are the next steps from your side?”


If needed to show seriousness use 
“If needed, I’m happy to seek external advice to understand the best way to resolve this.”


